<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('./partials/head', { title: 'Introduction' }) %>

    <body>
        <%- include('./partials/sidebar', { activePage: 'intro' }) %>

            <main class="main-content">
                <div class="content-container">

                    <ul class="breadcrumbs">
                        <li>Overview</li>
                        <li class="current">Introduction</li>
                    </ul>

                    <header>
                        <span class="badge">Version <%= version %></span>
                        <h1>
                            <%= title %>
                        </h1>
                        <p>
                            This guide explains how to use the Automation Portal without guessing, improvising,
                            or sending “quick questions” to whoever looks busiest.
                        </p>
                    </header>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>What this portal is</h2>
                        <p>
                            The Automation Portal centralizes internal requests, workflow-driven approvals, and
                            operational task routing.
                            Instead of requests living in inboxes, chats, or someone’s memory, the portal captures
                            requests as structured
                            submissions and drives them through assigned tasks until work is complete.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The platform is built around three simple ideas:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Forms</strong> capture information in a consistent way.</li>
                            <li><strong>Workflows</strong> coordinate multi-step processes across multiple people.</li>
                            <li><strong>Tasks</strong> make accountability unavoidable (in a healthy, professional way).
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>Who this guide is for</h2>
                        <p>
                            This documentation is split so each audience can find what they need without reading
                            everything:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>End Users:</strong> Submit requests, complete assigned tasks, and track
                                progress.</li>
                            <li><strong>Administrators:</strong> Configure forms, manage workflows, monitor runs, and
                                review responses.</li>
                            <li><strong>Developers:</strong> Integrate with the platform APIs and use Swagger
                                documentation.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>Main navigation</h2>
                        <p>
                            The sidebar is the primary way to move through the portal. Below is a direct map of the core
                            areas and their
                            endpoints.
                        </p>

                        <table class="doc-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Menu</th>
                                    <th>Purpose</th>
                                    <th>Endpoint</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Home</td>
                                    <td>Entry point and high-level overview.</td>
                                    <td><code>/</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Workflows</td>
                                    <td>Browse workflow templates and monitor workflow execution (admin-managed runs).
                                    </td>
                                    <td><code>/workflows</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>My Tasks</td>
                                    <td>Your assigned workflow items. This is where you do actual work when assigned.
                                    </td>
                                    <td><code>/my-tasks</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Self Service</td>
                                    <td>Standalone forms for one-off requests (not tied to a workflow run).</td>
                                    <td><code>/self-service</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Responses</td>
                                    <td>Admin-only review of submitted and pending form responses.</td>
                                    <td><code>/responses</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Dashboard</td>
                                    <td>Operational visibility and summary reporting.</td>
                                    <td><code>/dashboard</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Configuration</td>
                                    <td>Admin configuration area for system setup and management.</td>
                                    <td><code>/configuration</code></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Docs</td>
                                    <td>This documentation site.</td>
                                    <td><code>/docs</code></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <div class="panel panel-info">
                            <div class="panel-title">Access differences</div>
                            <p>
                                Some pages (like <strong>Responses</strong> and <strong>Configuration</strong>) are
                                restricted to admins.
                                If you don’t see an item in the sidebar, it usually means your role does not have
                                access.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>How work flows through the portal</h2>
                        <p>
                            Most activity in the portal falls into one of two paths:
                        </p>

                        <h3>1) Self Service requests</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>You open <code>/self-service</code> and submit a standalone form.</li>
                            <li>Your submission becomes a response record that admins can review in
                                <code>/responses</code>.
                            </li>
                            <li>If follow-up is needed, admins can email you directly from the response record.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3>2) Workflow-driven work</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>An admin launches a workflow (template → run).</li>
                            <li>The run generates assignable items (tasks) for specific users.</li>
                            <li>Assigned items show up for users under <code>/my-tasks</code>.</li>
                            <li>Admins monitor and manage the run from <code>/workflows</code>.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>Where to start</h2>
                        <p>
                            If you are new, start here: <a href="/docs/getting-started">Getting Started</a> for login
                            and first-time navigation.
                        </p>

                    </section>

                    <section class="doc-section">
                        <h2>Developer</h2>
                        <p>
                            The Automation Portal exposes API endpoints for integration and automation. Interactive API
                            documentation is
                            available via Swagger.
                        </p>

                        <div class="panel panel-info">
                            <div class="panel-title">Swagger API Docs</div>
                            <p>
                                Access Swagger documentation at: <code>/api-docs</code>
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <p>
                            Swagger includes:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Available endpoints and request parameters</li>
                            <li>Authentication requirements</li>
                            <li>Request/response models</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <footer style="margin-top: 3rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #6b7280;">
                        <p>Generated at <%= new Date().toLocaleString() %>
                        </p>
                    </footer>

                </div>
            </main>
    </body>

</html>